messages.content:
Place a shunt resistor (R_shunt) in the high side of the load.

Pinout / wiring:
- Vin+ -> 5V supply
- Vin- -> load V+ (this is the bus voltage you also read)
- Across Vin+ and Vin- is the shunt resistor (e.g. 0.1 ohm)
- VCC of the INA219 -> 3.3 V (it tolerates 3-5.5 V on VCC; the bus can be up to 26 V)
- GND -> GND
- SCL/SDA -> MCU I2C with 4.7 k pull-ups
- A0/A1 -> tied to GND for I2C address 0x40

Code (Adafruit_INA219):

```cpp
#include <Adafruit_INA219.h>
Adafruit_INA219 ina;
void setup() { Serial.begin(115200); ina.begin(); }
void loop() {
  Serial.print(ina.getBusVoltage_V()); Serial.print(" V, ");
  Serial.print(ina.getCurrent_mA());   Serial.println(" mA");
  delay(500);
}
```

Resolution with the default 0.1 ohm shunt is 0.1 mA. For sub-mA resolution use a 0.5 ohm shunt and the 16x gain config.
